event.title: arrived in the area on February 15, 1881

data.event: The first settlers were J. William Schoellmann and his family, who arrived in the area on February 15, 1881.
The first church in Nada was dedicated on October 7, 1897 and a schoolhouse was constructed in 1899 that housed eighteen students.
